assimilate

public void assimilate(Workflow.Approval app)
Assimilate state from a running Workflow. This is intended to be called only for leaf approvals after 5.0. If this is used again with parent approvals, there will need to be a smarter plan about deriving a "phase" or something to stick into the request to track location in the hierarchy.

isApproved

public boolean isApproved()
Return true if the this is a simple item whose completion state should be rendered as "Approved" rather than "Finished". There is no WorkItem.State meaning Approved, it is either Finished or Rejected. With the newer work items for granular approvals and manual actions "Finished" can mean several things.

getTypeKey

public java.lang.String getTypeKey()

getStateKey

public java.lang.String getStateKey()
JSF Helper - return the message key of the work item state. This one is a little more complicated so the "Approved" status can be inserted.
